reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great case, much value, such nice.
reviews.reviewText: In the picture you can see our house is extremely dusty (3 air purifiers active and we vacuum, mop and dust daily) as we are in Southwest NM with two dogs awaiting cedar mulch. The case hasn’t let ANY dust in after 5 days of heavy use. I vacuum out the front vents when I vacuum the house and it’s effortless from there. My old case was a Thor v2, it was massive and had amazing airflow, but I wanted something more compact and visually pleasing. For the money this thing is perfect.Pros: CLEAN and stays that way with minimal care. Easy to build, I mean painless. Majority of cables already tied down, all I had to do was run PSU cables, plug in case wires, and plug in Satas. Took me an hour to build this thing. Plenty of room for a massive cpu cooler and a huge GPU. Magnetic filter on top is a wonderful touch too!Con (yes only one): I had to install a 140mm fan on the top pulling air out of the case, this was largely to blame on my cpu cooler and GPU’s close proximity. That being said one fan fixed all of my problems, I’m running a 10900k and a 1080ti and neither run very hot with no AC hooked up yet. Cpu average:80-85c GPU: 71-75c

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love it looks nice, helped on my gpu temps to drop. Happy that it came with 3 fans that I used as a supply for my GPU.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The case style and appearance. Love the LED feature.
reviews.reviewText: I was not happy with my current PC Case. Not very attractive, plain black with orange light. I purchased this case and I must say I am more than pleased. The fans look great and are not very loud. I enjoyed the build. Lots of room for cable management!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great case, only two drawbacks.
reviews.reviewText: So to start... Excellent quality, plenty of room, RGB lights are nice and quiet, cable management is amazing... I love how easy it was to get my build set up, and the room left over after using a full ATX motherboard and GPU was great.Only two things I would say are bad about this case, and that's why I'm leaving 4 stars instead of 5. No included 3.5" trays. I just spent $73 on this case, and they couldn't include at least one tray? So now I'll have to figure out which tray will fit and spend even more money to add it. Second, the triangle shaped "Tempered Glass" sticker was applied directly to the glass. It's not a vinyl peel off, it's a full blown sticker, so after getting done with my build, I spent almost 15 minutes with a Razer and nail polish remover to get the left over sticky crap off the glass.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy enough for me to connect
reviews.reviewText: I'm a dad that's slowly losing touch with what's up to date. This was for my young son and we learned about the insides of a computer and what does what while we assembled this build together. I haven't delved in PC assembly in almost 15 years but of course had to act like I knew exactly what I was doing with my boy (mostly joking) but I managed to get it up and running all together in about an hour. It's a beautiful case and super quiet to boot!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 30, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Love this case super quite , colors true many different light settings , easy to work with would definitely recommended to others Great Product..A++

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price
reviews.reviewText: I've been using this case for about a month now, and I haven't had any issues with it so far (aside from the sticker they put on the glass panel). It's extremely quiet, to the point that I can only tell when it's on because of the fan RGB. Cable management was easy (as long as nobody looks inside the back panel). Everything worked on my first attempt. My only complaint is that there's no chassis for a HDD.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for the price.
reviews.reviewText: Easy to use for build. Stock fans are good enough. Case works well with a B450 board (connections, etc). Did not encounter any sharp edges during build. I did remove the lower 3.5" hard drive cage to make room for cable management.
I bought this for my son as he wants to build his own PC. He was very happy with it.

It’s a decent case, it uses glass cover instead of plastic. All the fans are pre-installed.Only issue I have is the fan doesn’t connect to system fan port on motherboard. And because I have an older board, it can only power by HDD power, which cause the fan working at full power whenever I turn on my pc.
